President Biden and President Macron of France held a state visit at the White House. President Biden acknowledged France as the United States' oldest ally and praised their enduring friendship. They discussed the importance of the alliance between France and the United States, particularly in facing challenges such as Russia's aggression against Ukraine and the climate crisis. Both leaders emphasized the shared commitment to liberty, justice, and democratic values. They also highlighted the need to work together to address global issues and build a better future for future generations. The visit was seen as an opportunity to strengthen the alliance between the two countries and promote cooperation in various areas.